 <section class="sec-lg bg-slate-50 border-t border-slate-100">
 <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
 <div class="text-center mb-16 reveal">
 <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-black text-slate-900 uppercase italic tracking-tighter mb-4">Wireless Charging <span class="text-brandOrange">FAQ</span></h2>
 <p class="text-slate-500 font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-[11px]">Technical insights for wholesale buyers</p>
 </div>
 <div class="space-y-4">
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Do your wireless chargers support 15W fast charging for Android?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. Our Qi2-certified models support 15W MPP (Magnetic Power Profile) for both the latest iPhones and compatible Android flagship devices including Samsung Galaxy S24, Google Pixel 8, and other Qi2-enabled devices. Qi2 is a universal open standard — no MFi licensing required.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is the MOQ for custom branded wireless chargers?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">For standard ODM models with custom logos, our MOQ starts at <strong>500 units</strong>. For full private tooling (OEM), it starts at <strong>2,000 units</strong>. Sample turnaround: 3-7 days for standard models. Flexible MOQ options for startup brands available.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is the difference between Qi and Qi2?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Qi2 is the latest WPC standard featuring Apple's Magnetic Power Profile (MPP). Unlike original Qi which only guaranteed 5W for Android, Qi2 provides <strong>15W universal fast charging</strong> with secure magnetic alignment using N52H neodymium magnets. Qi2.2 (ratified 2025-07) extends to 25W with active cooling. No Apple MFi licensing required — Qi2 is fully open.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Do your wireless chargers support Samsung and Apple simultaneous charging?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. Our 3-in-1 charging docks support simultaneous fast charging for iPhone (15W/25W Qi2 MPP), Apple Watch (2.5-5W), and AirPods/TWS (5W). Samsung users get the same 15W fast charge for Galaxy phones, plus 5W for Galaxy Watch and Galaxy Buds. Qi2 universal standard means both ecosystems charge at full speed.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What magnets do you use for Qi2 magnetic compatibility?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">We use <strong>N52H grade neodymium magnets</strong>, the strongest commercial grade available — up to 1400g suction force on our car mount line. This ensures a secure snap and consistent alignment even with protective cases up to 3mm thickness. Our magnetic force meets or exceeds Apple's official MagSafe specifications.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is Qi2.2 and when will 25W wireless chargers be available?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Qi2.2 (Qi v2.2.1) was ratified in July 2025, extending wireless charging from 15W to <strong>25W MPP</strong>. WOWOHCOOL currently ships 25W Qi2.2 models in the 3-in-1 (WOW10, WOW18, WOW19, WOW122, WOW125, WOW133, WOW115) and car mount (WOW41) lines. Qi2.2 25W desktop pad and stand launching Q3 2026 with pre-registration open now.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What certifications do your wireless chargers come with?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">All models are <strong>WPC Qi2 certified</strong> (15W/25W MPP), <strong>CE</strong> (EMC + Low Voltage Directive) for EU, <strong>FCC Part 15</strong> for US, and <strong>RoHS + REACH</strong> compliant. Car mount models are E-Mark (ECE R10) ready. Full certification documentation package — including CE DoC, FCC test reports, and Qi2 WPC ATL compliance — provided with every OEM order.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">How long does OEM/ODM wireless charger production take?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">OEM (standard models with custom logo): <strong>25-30 days</strong> after sample approval. ODM (custom enclosure or exclusive design): <strong>45-60 days</strong> including tooling and Qi2 certification prep. Both include 4-stage QC (IQC → IPQC → FQC → OQC) with 4-hour 100% aging test. Air freight: 5-7 days. Seafreight: 25-35 days.</p>
 </details>
 </div>
